{{Quote|I am just better equipped to be helping people who actually need help.|Malcolm Ducasse to [[Zaya Okonjo]]|AKA Hero Pants}}
'''Malcolm Joseph Ducasse''' is a private investigator and an ally of [[Jessica Jones]] who was exploited by [[Kilgrave]], who turned him into a drug addict, to stalk Jones. Jones discovered Ducasse's involvement in Kilgrave's plan and helped him to go off of the drugs Kilgrave used to coerce him. Then, Ducasse became one of Jones' closest allies in putting a stop to Kilgrave's plan. He also started a [[Kilgrave Victim Support Group|support group]] for other victims of Kilgrave's manipulation, and once Kilgrave was finally stopped by Jones, Ducasse began to work with her as her associate at [[Alias Investigations]].

Now an investigator with Alias, Ducasse helped Jones track down [[John Raymond]], and was brought in for questioning about Jones and Raymond by [[Misty Knight]]. Ducasse and [[Trish Walker]], alongside other allies of the [[Defenders]], went into hiding at the [[29th Precinct Police Station]] due to their ties to the [[Hand]], who the Defenders ultimately defeated.

Jones later sought Ducasse's help in investigating [[IGH]], a shady company with ties to Jones' superpowers, as well as being recruited by [[Jeri Hogarth]] to dig up dirt on her [[Linda Chao|law]] [[Steven Benowitz|partners]], all the while starting a relationship with Walker. However, Walker, growing jealous of Jones, kidnapped the [[Karl Malus|doctor]] who gave Jones her powers, threatening Ducasse and stuffing him into the trunk of a car for trying to stop her. Growing tensions between Ducasse and Jones caused him to leave Alias Investigations, instead becoming a part of Hogarth's new firm, [[Hogarth & Associates]].

At Hogarth & Associates, Ducasse started a relationship with colleague [[Zaya Okonjo]], but found himself distressed by the practices employed at the firm. Jones turned to Ducasse once more with help protecting [[Brianna Gelden]], who was at risk of being targeted by [[Gregory Sallinger]], and again became involved with Walker, who had become a superpowered vigilante, though Ducasse's involvement with Walker cost him his relationship with Okonjo. Ultimately, Ducasse rejoined Alias Investigations, working with Jones to stop Walker, who had become a murderer. Jones was forced to stop and arrest Walker, prompting a distraught Jones to knock on Ducasse's door and hand him the keys to Alias, warning him not to mess it up.

==Biography==
===Early Life===
====Wanting to Help People====
{{Quote|They're idiots and I'm just the only asshole in the world that didn't know it?|Malcolm Ducasse|AKA I've Got the Blues}}
Malcolm Ducasse grew up in a household that was conscientious toward helping others. His mother said prayers in church for the sick and dying; his father worked on community projects for the poor. These experiences helped to shape an individual who desired to help others and abhorred selfishness.{{Ref|JJ111}}

====University====
Ducasse went to college on a full ride, making his parents proud. He met a woman named [[Nichelle]] and the two dated for awhile. Ducasse always found himself at parties.{{Ref|JJ206}} While out and about one evening, Ducasse was cornered by two thieves demanding his wallet. They beat him up and decided to kill Ducasse before [[Jessica Jones]] arrived to stop them. Before she could help him any further, [[Kilgrave]] arrived and took off with her.{{Ref|JJ105}}

===Kilgrave's Slave===
====Stalking Jessica Jones====
Once Jones was released from Kilgrave's control, Kilgrave found Ducasse and put him under his control. Ducasse became a junkie and Kilgrave became his primary source of drugs, which the latter supplied in exchange for pictures of Jones. Ducasse spied on her and even moved into her [[Jessica Jones' Apartment Building|apartment building]]. Ducasse and Kilgrave met everyday around 10 in the morning at varying locations for the exchange.{{Ref|JJ105}} As Ducasse's addiction became worse, [[Nichelle]] decided to break up with him and Ducasse was put on academic leave.{{Ref|JJ206}}

====Creamy Peanut Butter====
[[File:Malcolm-WrongApartment.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ducasse in [[Jessica Jones]]' apartment]]
{{Quote|God damn it, Malcolm. You scared the shit out of me."<br>"What are you doing in my [[Malcolm Ducasse's Apartment|apartment]]?"<br>"[[Alias Investigations Office|This]] is my apartment.|[[Jessica Jones]] and Malcolm Ducasse|AKA Ladies Night}}
One morning, Ducasse mistakenly entered [[Jessica Jones]]' [[Alias Investigations Office|apartment]] instead of his own, went into her refrigerator, and, with a knife, began eating her peanut butter, noting that it was creamy, not crunchy, as he usually had. Jones approached him, causing Ducasse to jump back in shock and ask why she was in his apartment; Jones corrected him. Jones then escorted him from her apartment as a couple knocked on the door, wondering if they had found Jones in order to hire her as a P.I.

A few days later, Ducasse entered the elevator that contained Jones and noticed that she looked disheveled; Jones told him that she was in need of money, so Ducasse offered her a television that he had stolen earlier. Jones refused the offer and rode silently beside Ducasse.{{Ref|JJ101}}

====Hearing Noise====
Ducasse heard the arguments of [[Robyn]] and [[Ruben]] on the floor above his apartment; Ducasse was so high though that he could not distinguish those sounds from his own mental chaos. As he stepped into the hallway, he saw [[Jessica Jones]] passing and asked her which was true; she told him both.{{Ref|JJ102}}

====Creating Distractions====
{{Quote|You're a good person, Jessica Jones."<br>"You're high.|Malcolm Ducasse and [[Jessica Jones]]|AKA It's Called Whiskey}}
Ducasse was high one day when he attempted to cross a street; a [[Holden|bicyclist]] nearly collided with him and fell from his bicycle. Though Ducasse apologized profusely, the bicyclist cornered and lectured him about their differences. [[Jessica Jones]] saw the confrontation and grabbed the bicyclist, forcing him to leave Ducasse alone and continue his journey.

Later, Ducasse was hungry and went to the [[Robyn's Apartment|apartment]] of [[Robyn]] and [[Ruben]] while she slept to obtain peanut butter. His presence scared Robyn, but Ruben escorted him from the apartment downstairs. As they entered the fifth floor of the [[Jessica Jones' Apartment Building|apartment building]], Ducasse was given instructions on how to walk by Ruben who was holding him upright. Jones came over to assist and placed Ducasse inside [[Malcolm Ducasse's Apartment|his apartment]].

Soon after, Jones took Ducasse to a hospital; he did not understand why he was there because he felt that he only needed sleep and he disliked hospitals. Suddenly, Jones pushed him down and he collided with a nurse pushing a medicine cart. Ducasse and the nurse were surrounded by others who attempted to help them. As Ducasse sat with someone assisting him, Jones looked towards him as she left the hospital.{{Ref|JJ103}}

The next day, Ducasse was attempting to enter his apartment, but could not find the right key; he worked on locating the right key on his keychain for almost five minutes. Meanwhile, a [[Audrey Eastman|woman]] stood outside the [[Alias Investigations Office]]. Jones walked and spoke briefly to the woman before letting her inside. Jones then approached Ducasse and used a key she had to let him inside his place. When Jones asked about his welfare, he wondered why she was asking; she said that she did not want to be his excuse to get high. Ducasse told her that he did not need a reason.{{Ref|JJ104}}

====Suspected to Spying====
Ducasse was at the entrance of [[Jessica Jones' Apartment Building]] when [[Jessica Jones]] and [[Will Simpson]] entered. Simpson noticed that Ducasse seemed to be observing them and demanded to know what Ducasse was doing. Jones separated the two and told Ducasse to get some sleep; Ducasse noted that Simpson did not like him.

Inside [[Malcolm Ducasse's Apartment|his apartment]], Ducasse left pictures of Jones on his printer.{{Ref|JJ104}}

====Followed to Kilgrave====
[[File:Jessica Jones - 1x05 - AKA The Sandwich Saved Me - Malcolm and Kilgrave (1).png|{{AltFloat}}|Ducasse and [[Kilgrave]] meeting at the kiosk]]
Every morning, a quarter to 10:00, Ducasse performed his usual routine of visiting [[Kilgrave]] for the exchange. Unbeknownst to him, he was being tailed by [[Jessica Jones]]. Ducasse briefly stopped at the center of the park before meeting with Kilgrave at the section of the park where the older fellas play chess. Ducasse handed Kilgrave a large yellow envelope, and in return, Kilgrave handed him back a smaller one. The following morning, a quarter to 10:00, Ducasse went back to the park, where a woman under the compulsion of Kilgrave told him to meet him at the kiosk. At a new stand in [[Central Park]], he stood by as the stand owner scolded and insulted Kilgrave, witnessing as Kilgrave then commanded the owner to throw hot coffee in his face before walking away.
[[File:Jessica Jones - 1x05 - AKA The Sandwich Saved Me - Malcolm and Kilgrave (2).png|{{AltFloat}}|Ducasse and Kilgrave spot [[Jessica Jones]]]]
Days later, like clockwork, a quarter to 10:00, Ducasse went to meet with Kilgrave, first stopping in the park, where he got word of Kilgrave's location from someone under his compulsion. Still, Ducasse remained unaware that he was being followed by Jones. Ducasse then met with Kilgrave outside a cafe, with Jones not far behind, and her team, waiting for her word to act. Just like before, Ducasse handed over a large orange envelope and Kilgrave gave him back a smaller one in return. Before they could complete the transaction, Jones arrived just as Kilgrave is shot with a tranquilizer.{{Ref|JJ105}}

===Saving Himself===
====Jessica Jones' Test====
Ducasse returned to [[Malcolm Ducasse's Apartment|his apartment]] and called [[Tweaky]] to bring him a supply of drugs, since he did not get the drugs that [[Kilgrave]] usually provided; Tweaky arrived, but became upset upon learning that Ducasse did not have any money. He tried to bargain with the drug dealer, telling her that she could have his television and computer printer in exchange for the supply; Tweaky laughed, citing that she did not need a printer and her television was better. Ducasse became anxious and thrashed his arms; the sudden move caused Tweaky to draw her gun and threaten to castrate Ducasse if he continued to act up. Suddenly, [[Jessica Jones]] entered the apartment and disarmed Tweaky. As Jones escorted Tweaky out, the drug dealer taunted Ducasse by saying that if Jones had money, she could buy the drugs for him.
[[File:Malcolm.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Ducasse suffers the withdrawal symptoms in [[Alias Investigations Office|Jones' bathroom]]]]
As Ducasse attempted to go after her, Jones proceeded to throw him against his bed; Ducasse told her that she could not save him again this time. Jones proceeded to handcuff Ducasse to the toilet in her bathroom to keep him from attempting to get high. Without the drugs, Ducasse's body began to suffer. Ducasse attempted to convince Jones that he was no longer a good person, pointing out that most of the time he took pictures of her for Kilgrave just so he would supply him with the drugs. Jones then proceeded to explain to Ducasse that during the months that she was enthralled by Kilgrave, that there was some part of her willpower that fought to escape from him and that she was still fighting. She further revealed that if Ducasse gave up on himself, then she will lose as Kilgrave only ruined him so that she would have another death on her hands. Jones presented him a choice: fight the addiction and become an altruistic and kind human being again or take the drugs that she had paid for him. After some initial thought, Ducasse took Jones words to heart and fought his addiction the entire night and threw the drugs away, effectively setting him on the path of getting himself clean through willpower.{{Ref|JJ105}}
[[File:Jessica Jones - 1x06 - AKA You're a Winner! - Jessica and Malcolm.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ducasse and [[Jessica Jones]] discuss [[Kilgrave]]]]
Ducasse, still with [[Jessica Jones]], explained the beauty behind [[Kilgrave]]'s powers. No one knows how he does it. It can't be explained, so it can't be believed, though Jones only needed to know where he did it, so that she could catch him. Ducasse suggested that they pool their information on Kilgrave so that maybe they could hone in on his limitations. However, Jones was far past discussing Kilgrave. Then, there was a knock at the door. On the other side was [[Luke Cage]]. He wanted to hire Jones. However, Ducasse did not trust Cage, as he suspected that he might've been under Kilgrave's compulsion. As it turned out, he wasn't, and Jones sent Ducasse home.
[[File:Jessica Jones - 1x06 - AKA You're a Winner! - Luke and Malcolm.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ducasse questioning [[Luke Cage]]]]
Ducasse approached Cage to ask if he's been approached by Kilgrave as he still remained uncertain that Cage was acting of his own free will. Cage seemed baffled by Ducasse's line of questioning, though he could tell that Ducasse was interested in Jones. And so, he warned him to tread lightly and not get attached. Ducasse then told Cage to reserve whatever issues he had as Jones had already been through hell, and saved Ducasse from the same. Cage asked if this hell he referred to had anything to do with Kilgrave, which it did.
[[File:Jessica Jones - 1x06 - AKA You're a Winner! - Malcolm.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ducasse attending survivors meeting]]
The following morning, Ducasse revealed to Jones that he attended one of the meetings for the Kilgrave survivors as Jones had previously suggested. That night, Ducasse attended another meeting for the Kilgrave survivors. He shared his story with them, how Kilgrave turned him into a liar, addict, and thief. However, the question remained if that was in Ducasse to begin with or if that's part of who he is now.{{Ref|JJ106}}

====Helping Jessica Jones====
Ducasse helped [[Jessica Jones]] back to her apartment after finding her drunk on the elevator. In her bed, they found [[Ruben]]'s body. The bed soaked in blood and in Ruben's hand, a knife. [[Kilgrave]] made him kill himself. Ducasse wanted to call the police, but with this being the third death that Jones was connected to, she feared the police would arrest her. Jones could only think of one way to stop Kilgrave, and that was for her to be sent to the super max prison, a hi-tech mousetrap, where he'd inevitably come for her. Ducasse tried to talk Jones out of it, but she needed proof of Kilgrave using his powers. Before going, she needed to get her affairs in order, and she wanted Ducasse to disappear as she could no longer protect him.

Instead of disappearing as Jones told him, Ducasse returned to her apartment. He was spotted by [[Robyn]] as he exited her apartment. Robyn suspected that something was going on between Jones and her brother. Ducasse claimed that they were involved.

Ducasse called [[Trish Walker]] over to Jones' apartment, where he revealed to her that Kilgrave killed Ruben. And he needed Walker's help to stop Jones from turning herself in at 8:00 PM. After leaning up the blood, Ducasse took the body down to the docks, where he dumped it into the river. Jones found him soon thereafter. She jumped into the river, recovered Ruben's head and proceeded with her plan.{{Ref|JJ107}}

====Search for Ruben====
Knowing of [[Ruben]]'s demise, Ducasse continued to keep his death a secret from [[Robyn]], helping her out in posting flyers around the area for any information on Ruben's whereabouts.

One night with the remaining members of the [[Kilgrave Victim Support Group]], Ducasse asked around if anyone wanted to continue to share their story. When no one volunteered, he willingly shared his story, mentioning his recent help with [[Jessica Jones|a friend]]; he told them that [[Kilgrave]] had planned to frame her for the death of their neighbor and that he kept it a secret for a while, having dumped his body in the river. Unaware, Robyn revealed that she had heard everything and intervened. Distraught, she quickly blamed Ducasse for betraying her in dumping his body and attack the group for their lack of anger for what they had gone through. Robyn continued to question Jones and her lack in informing the group on Kilgrave. Rebelling against Ducasse's wishes, she managed to bring [[Donald]] and [[Jackson]] alongside her to storm [[Alias Investigations Office]] to attack Jones.

Only seconds ahead of them, Ducasse warned Jones that Robyn and two others were planning to attack. While Robyn had knocked Jones unconscious, Ducasse was unable to fend off Jackson and Donald. Now, a freed Kilgrave, Ducasse, Robyn, Donald, and Jackson were enthralled and taken away.{{Ref|JJ110}}

====Enthralled Again====
Unbeknownst to Ducasse, [[Robyn]] followed him to his support group, and after hearing him confess to lying and disposing of [[Ruben]]'s body, Robyn rallied [[Donald]] and [[Jackson]], and together the three of them barged into [[Alias Investigations Office|Jones' apartment]] and attacked her. In the back, Robyn found [[Kilgrave]] and set him free.

At [[Niku]], he, alongside Donald, Jackson, and Robyn, were forced to stand atop a counter with nooses around their necks. They watched as [[Kilgrave]] dined with [[Hope Shlottman]] by his side. Eventually, [[Jessica Jones]] arrived with [[Albert Thompson]]. While the two negotiated, Kilgrave ordered the four to step forward when Jones threatened to harm him. After Thompson was forced to walk to his son's side, Jones had believed that Shlottman would free; however, when Shlottman broke a wine glass and used the stub to stab her neck, Ducasse and the others did as commanded and stepped forward, unable to free themselves. Jones managed to knock the pipe from the ceiling and grounded the victims before rushing to Shlottman, unable to save her from bleeding out. Ducasse comforted Robyn, having experienced Kilgrave's control.{{Ref|JJ110}}

After Jones cleaned her hands of Shlottman's blood, she quickly tried to persuade the others to follow along and tell the police a lie: a girl came into Niku, had too many drinks, and willingly committed suicide before they could intervene. Despite a few protests, Ducasse convinced everyone to do so. Each told the story before separating.

Ducasse arranged another group meeting, but no one showed, with the exception of Robyn, who only came to warn him to stop group-texting his location to a bunch of strangers. She feared Kilgrave could've gotten to any of them. As far as Robyn was concerned, no one could help anyone, but Ducasse refused to believe that. Ducasse returned to his apartment, where he saw that someone had broken into Jones' place. He contemplated calling her, but ultimately decided to go one about his business.{{Ref|JJ111}}

===Robyn===
Later, Ducasse informed Jones that he was leaving [[New York City]] after developing feeling lonely since meeting her. Ready to leave [[Malcolm Ducasse's Apartment|his apartment]], he heard [[Robyn]] arguing with a postal delivery woman upstairs and escalates the situation, informing Robyn that the package was for [[Ruben]]. Sitting alongside her, he listened to her speak about Ruben.

Ducasse brought Robyn to the dump site, allowing her to say a prayer.{{Ref|JJ111}}

===[[Alias Investigations]]===
====Private Investigator====
Having been freed by [[Jeri Hogarth]], [[Jessica Jones]] returned to [[Alias Investigations Office|her apartment-office]], stressed yet relieved that she had removed [[Kilgrave]] as a threat. Receiving a load of voice mails and calls from potential clients demanding her help, Jones sat at her desk, too drained to give any of them a response; Ducasse approached her phone and answered a call for Jones, asking the caller how the agency could help with their case.{{Ref|JJ113}}

Now sober, Ducasse called [[Nichelle]] to apologize, but got no answer as she did not believe he was forced to become an addict.{{Ref|JJ206}}

====John Raymond's Case====
[[File:TD101 MalcolmDucasse01.png|{{AltFloat}}||Malcolm helps [[Jessica Jones]] in locating the origin of the call]]
Letting himself inside [[Alias Investigations Office]], Ducasse took the kitchen, informing [[Jessica Jones]] that he was only there for a soda. He traveled, however, to Jones and glanced over her shoulder at her laptop, questioning if she had taken another case. Requesting he not be by her shoulder, she informed Ducasse that she originally did not want to take the case but received a call warning that Jones not take the case on. He recommended that she should attempt to trace where the call was made. After learning it originated from a payphone, Ducasse disclosed a place he used to visit during his enthrall; Jones grabbed her jacket and left, asking Ducasse to leave as she went.{{Ref|TD101}}
[[File:TD102 JessicaJones01.png|{{AltFloat}}|Malcolm is held hostage while [[Jessica Jones]] attempts to de-escalate [[John Raymond]]]]
When Jones returned to her apartment building, she takes note that the door was ajar and becomes alert. Entering inside, she sighed, believing it was Ducasse letting himself inside. However, she found Ducasse is taken hostage by her suspect [[John Raymond]]. As Jones tried to disengage Raymond, Ducasse made a comment that he was barely on the payroll for working for [[Alias Investigations]]. Soon, everyone witnessed as [[Elektra]] slashed the locks and Raymond fire a bullet into his head. Though Ducasse asked if Jones was well, she stormed after Elektra.{{Ref|TD102}} Both Jones and Ducasse are taken into police custody for questioning.{{Ref|TD103}}

====Under Police Protection====
[[File:TD105 WingDucasseTempleWalker.png|{{AltFloat}}|Malcolm and the others listen to an announcement from [[Misty Knight]]]]
Under the request of [[Jessica Jones]], Ducasse went to the [[29th Precinct Police Station]], meeting with [[Trish Walker]]. He sat next to her and was asked by Walker if he knew that Jones had connections with [[Daredevil]]; she also believed that [[New York City Earthquake|the tremors]] were associated with the people that threatened them. They then saw [[New York Bulletin]] writer, [[Karen Page]] walked in. They were confused on her connection to this event. [[Misty Knight]] then came in asking for their cooperation.{{Ref|TD105}} When the [[Defenders]] escaped, Ducasse and [[Foggy Nelson]] got word that they were at [[Midland Circle]]. They rushed in to tell Walker and Page. Walker informed them that it was the epicenter of the earthquake. They listened to the radio dispatcher tell officers to evacuate the building. Soon, Midland collapsed, defeating the [[Hand]]. Ducasse and Walker comforted Jones as she walked in. However, they lost [[Daredevil]] in the battle.{{Ref|TD108}}

====Continuing to Help====
{{Quote|You take the day off."<br>"Thanks, but I need to work, or I get myself into trouble. It's an addict thing.|[[Jessica Jones]] and Malcolm Ducasse|AKA Freak Accident}}
Ducasse, once more, stood inside [[Alias Investigations Office]]. Standing in a chair, he told [[Jessica Jones]] that he figured he would try to fix the gunshot patches in the wall, brushing plaster across the holes.{{Ref|TD108}}
[[File:Jones meeting Pryce Cheng.png|{{AltFloat}}|[[Pryce Cheng]] proposes a buyout]]
Continuing to make repairs to the wall, Ducasse aided in keeping track of cases that walk into the office. He woke Jones up and gave her a drink, telling her to chug it. He then opened the blinds to get her ready for her clients. She simply told him he was fired, but he did not listen. He then listened as a man named [[Whizzer]] explained he was being hunted. When Jones turned him down, Ducasse apologized. The two had an argument about her attitude before [[Pryce Cheng]] arrived and proposed a buyout. Jones told him off. Ducasse went back to work and patched up holes in the wall when [[Trish Walker]] came in and showed Jones a box. She asked Ducasse to leave, but Jones forced him to stay. Walker then opened the box, revealing Jones' family's ashes. Ducasse asked questions, so Jones "fired" him once again. He left for the day, telling her he would see her tomorrow.

The next day, Ducasse walked in and told Jones that Mrs. [[Belenka]] cancelled. He also gave Jones a package from Cheng. Suddenly, Whizzer knocked on the door again pleading for help, but Jones closed the door on him. Ducasse told her to be nicer. Jones then saw that Cheng's package was a bunch of files on himself and a note saying he was an open book. Ducasse tried to take notes on Cheng's idea of not having any hidden secrets, but Jones told him it was not a lesson.

That night, he returned to the office only to see the ashes on the ground as well as Jones crying and sitting on the ground. Ducasse went to help her, but she yelled at him for almost stepping on [[Phillip Jones|Phillip]]'s ashes. He used papers to clean everything up and Jones told him Phillip would have been his age. She then told Ducasse that Whizzer was murdered. Jones opened up Whizzer's bag and found drugs in it. She also realized that he could not remember his past, just like her. Jones decided to do research and told Ducasse to do the same. He found the location of [[Industrial Garments & Handling Facility]], a front for [[IGH]]. Jones went to investigate.{{Ref|JJ201}}

====Confronting Max Tatum====
[[File:Jessica Jones - 2x02 - AKA Freak Accident - Max and Malcolm.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ducasse confronted [[Max Tatum]]]]
{{Quote|Take my wallet. Here, here's the keys."<br>"I don't want your damn car. I want you to admit what you did to [[Trish Walker]]."<br>"Aw, listen, buddy. Whatever Trish told you, she's the one who started it. She crawled into my bed. Shit! You broke my nose!|[[Max Tatum]] and Malcolm Ducasse|AKA Freak Accident}}
Ducasse continued to do research and found out that [[Miklos Kozlov]] had died. He called [[Jessica Jones]] who went to the minyan for answers. She told Ducasse to take the day off, but he refused saying that he needs to work or he worries that he will turn back to drugs. He then got a ping from a woman named Annette. He proceeded to sleep with her.

Ducasse got a call from [[Trish Walker]], asking for his help in an investigation. She also asked that he keep this from Jones, They met on a movie set, where she asked Ducasse to record her interaction with [[Max Tatum]], during which time Walker demanded that he grant her access to [[Metro-General Hospital]]. Should he refuse, she threatened to go public about what happened between them. After learning he sexually abused Walker when she was 15 years old, he approached Tatum by his car and demanded that he confess. Tatum claimed that Walker started the incident when she crawled into his bed. This angered Ducasse so much that he punched Tatum.{{Ref|JJ202}}

====Eviction Notice====
[[File:JJ203c.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ducasse warns [[Jessica Jones]]]]
Ducasse woke up to find an eviction notice on [[Jessica Jones]]' door. It is illegal to run a business out of an apartment building. He showed it to Jones, saying they were screwed. He also asked if she got a hold of [[Trish Walker]]. Jones angrily walked away to talk to [[Oscar Arocho]]. Ducasse warned her not to do anything stupid before leaving to update his resume. He went to do some research and found that Arocho was convicted years ago. Ducasse then brought up how the old super was fired. Jones said that Arocho must have had dirt on him. Ducasse went to pay the old super a visit.
[[File:JJ203d.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ducasse meets the super]]
Ducasse found the old super only to figure out that he loves Arocho and that he created a painting for the super. Ducasse left after the man objectified him. Ducasse returned to Jones and they thought of other ways, one of them being to find more dirt on Arocho. Jones clogged her toilet to get Arocho distracted. Later, Ducasse was told to protect Walker. He went to her apartment posing as a paparazzi, even earning $200 for giving a fake tip to the other paparazzis. He then got in a car with Walker only to be knocked over by a very strong [[Alisa Jones|woman]]. Although Ducasse and Walker were okay, the woman escaped.{{Ref|JJ203}}
{{Clear}}

====Jones Arrested====
[[File:TrishMalcolmTabloid.PNG|{{AltFloat}}|Ducasse sees the magazine]]
Ducasse was working on [[Jessica Jones]]' walls when [[Pryce Cheng]] walked in and talked to Ducasse. Cheng condescended him, calling him an addict. This struck a chord with Ducasse who told him off as politely as he could. He then found a magazine that claimed [[Trish Walker]] was dating him, as they were seen nights before. He later slept with a woman and left briefly to talk to Jones about Cheng's visit. He then realized how under appreciated he was and demanded more salary and lessons. Jones respected him for this and granted his wishes. Ducasse then turned around and saw the woman who asked if she needed to leave. Ducasse said she could stay, but accidentally called her the wrong name, causing her to leave anyways.
[[File:RSundayStoppingTWalker.png|{{AltFloat}}|[[Jessica Jones]] is arrested]]
Later, Ducasse and a new woman walked into Jones' apartment for some booze. He saw the door unlocked and thought she was home. He then looked into her room and saw it was empty. Worried, he quickly turned on the lights to find that Jones had been robbed. Suddenly, there was commotion outside. Ducasse stepped out to find a [[Nick Spanos|man]] murdered. The police suspected Jones due to the strength necessary to kill him. Jones arrived after a night out with [[Trish Walker]]. Ducasse warned her, saying to run, but it was too late, the cops surrounded her. Before submitting herself, she told Ducasse that a woman named [[Inez Green]] was in the car. He needed to get her somewhere safe.{{Ref|JJ204}}
{{Clear}}

====Promoted====
[[Jessica Jones]] was eventually released from prison. When she returned, Ducasse with [[Inez Green]]. He showed Jones that he reorganized her place and bought her a new laptop using company money. She did not say anything and went straight to her booze, only to find it was gone. Ducasse pointed her to her shelf, where he stored the drinks. She asked him if he hid any more of her shit, showing no signs of gratefulness.

Later, Ducasse and Jones talked and she promoted him to associate. She then sent him to bring Green to [[Jeri Hogarth]]'s place to stay, but not before Ducasse got a kick from the news. He returned to his apartment to find his television as well as Green gone. He chased her down the street and told her that the only pawn shop that would sell a still hot television was across town. He then talked her into coming back with him. She dropped the television, shattering it. He then brought her to Hogarth's apartment and left her.{{Ref|JJ205}}

====Reuniting with Nichelle====
[[File:JJ206c.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ducasse talks to [[Nichelle]]]]
Ducasse was working when [[Jessica Jones]] walked in with what Ducasse immediately recognized as the walk of shame. He teased her for hooking up with [[Oscar Arocho]]. She showed him a picture of a man named [[Karl Malus]], who had relations with the woman known as [[Alisa Jones|Leslie Hansen]]. Jones pointed out that he had a wedding ring on, but Ducasse immediately recognized it as the university ring from his old college. Jones asked him to go back to get information. At the university, Ducasse approached his ex, [[Nichelle]], who wanted nothing to do with him. They talked and Ducasse apologized, admitting that he was an addict waiting to happen. During their conversation, Ducasse swiped her key card and used it to get a yearbook from Malus' year.
[[File:JJ206d.png|{{AltFloat}}|Ducasse has sex with [[Trish Walker]]]]
